 $\sim 290-320$ and $445 \mathrm{~cm}^{-1}$ appear, which could be assigned to $\mathrm{Au}-\mathrm{C}$ and $\mathrm{Au}-\mathrm{O}$ vibrations of carbenes 3, respectively, beside the Raman bands at 197, 396, 514 and $639 \mathrm{~cm}^{-1}$ corresponding to $\mathrm{TiO}_{2}$.\\
